<title>USA: Xcellenet says anticipates $600,000 charge.</title>
<headline>Xcellenet says anticipates $600,000 charge.</headline>
<dateline>ATLANTA 1997-07-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Xcellenet, a maker of computer networking and systems software, said late Wednesday it anticipates it will take $600,000 non-recurring charge against earnings.</p>
<p>The company said that the charge was the result streamling of its operations in the second quarter, which included the phasing out of 20 positions through normal attrition.</p>
<p>Xcellenet said it believes that a similar streamling opportunity exists in other areas of the company during the third quarter, and that will further lower fixed operating costs.</p>
<p>Seperately, Xcellenet reported a loss of $32,000 in the second quarter, compared to a profit of $363,000 or $0.05 a share in the same period a year ago.</p>
